HwMSTPEnabledStatus.description: A simple status value for the object.
HwMSTPEnabledStatus.name: HwMSTPEnabledStatus

hwMstp.contactinfo: VRP Team Huawei Technologies co.,Ltd. Huawei Bld.,NO.3 Xinxi Rd., Shang-Di Information Industry Base, Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China http://www.huawei.com Zip:100085
hwMstp.description: This module include the information about MSTP protocol in the bridge. The information can be read and some of them can be set.
hwMstp.name: hwMstp

hwMstpAccessoryEntry.description: The table entry of MSTP Accessory Information.
hwMstpAccessoryEntry.name: hwMstpAccessoryEntry

hwMstpAccessoryIndex.description: The index of the Accessory Commands of MSTP.
hwMstpAccessoryIndex.name: hwMstpAccessoryIndex

hwMstpAccessoryTable.description: The table of MSTP Accessory Information.
hwMstpAccessoryTable.name: hwMstpAccessoryTable

hwMstpAdminFormatSelector.description: The administrative Configuration Identifier Format Selector in use by the Bridge. This has a value of 0 indicate the format specified in the Standard of IEEE 802.1s. By default, the value is 0
hwMstpAdminFormatSelector.name: hwMstpAdminFormatSelector

hwMstpAdminMstID.description: Administrative Multiple spanning-tree instance Identifier. The relation between VLAN and Multiple spanning-tree instance is set by operation in the region, but it isn't effective if the configuration isn't actived. The scope of instance identifier is different, some versions are 0 to 48.
hwMstpAdminMstID.name: hwMstpAdminMstID

hwMstpAdminRegionName.description: This MSTP administrative region name. It changes to hwMstpOperRegionName when user use the activing command to active the configuration of the region.
hwMstpAdminRegionName.name: hwMstpAdminRegionName

hwMstpAdminRevisionLevel.description: This MSTP administrative revision level. It changes to hwMstpOperRevisionLevel when user use the activing command to active the configuration of the region. By default, the value is 0.
hwMstpAdminRevisionLevel.name: hwMstpAdminRevisionLevel

hwMstpBackupReplyAgreement.description: When the port of device, which played the backup or alternate role, receives the BPDU message with high priority, and the proposal flag of this message was set. The BPDU message can be send from this port immediately, the agreement flag was set of this BPDU message.
hwMstpBackupReplyAgreement.name: hwMstpBackupReplyAgreement

hwMstpBpduFilterPortDefault.description: When the stp BPDU-filter default is enabled. By default,the stp BPDU filter function is enabled .
hwMstpBpduFilterPortDefault.name: hwMstpBpduFilterPortDefault

hwMstpBpduGuard.description: Whether the Bridge BPDU Guard function is enabled. If the function is enabled, the port will shutdown when received BPDU and the port is configured as edgeport. The purpose of the function is to prevent the bridge from BPDU attacking. By default, the function is disabled
hwMstpBpduGuard.name: hwMstpBpduGuard

hwMstpBridgeInfoGroup.description: A collection of objects indicating the necessary capabilites of the bridge device which is running the multi spanning tree protocol.
hwMstpBridgeInfoGroup.name: hwMstpBridgeInfoGroup

hwMstpBridgeMaxHops.description: The maximum value of the Bridge hops. It can limit the scope of the bridge network. It is effective when the bridge is root bridge. The BPDU that the bridge receives from the Designed bridge will be dropped when the hops in the BPDU is zero . By default, the value is 20.
hwMstpBridgeMaxHops.name: hwMstpBridgeMaxHops

hwMstpCompliance.description: The compliance statement for device support of Priority and Multicast Filtering extended bridging services.
hwMstpCompliance.name: hwMstpCompliance

hwMstpConfigDegist.description: This MSTP region-configuration digest. It can be used to determine whether the region is the same region with another one.
hwMstpConfigDegist.name: hwMstpConfigDegist

hwMstpConfigDigestSnooping.description: This object indicates whether the digest snooping function is enabled on the port: 1: enabled 2: disabled By default, the function is not enabled. In other words, the default value is disabled(2).
hwMstpConfigDigestSnooping.name: hwMstpConfigDigestSnooping

hwMstpDefaultRegionName.description: Set default region name. The value of hwMstpDefaultRegionName is only unused(65535) when it is read. It is only reset(1) when it is set.
hwMstpDefaultRegionName.name: hwMstpDefaultRegionName

hwMstpDefaultVlanAllo.description: Set default configuration about VLAN allocation and all VLANs are mapped to CIST. The value of hwMstpDefaultVlanAllo is only unused(65535) when it is read. It is only enable(1) when it is set.
hwMstpDefaultVlanAllo.name: hwMstpDefaultVlanAllo

hwMstpDiameter.description: The diameter of Bridge. It stands for the scope of the network. It affects the time that include hello time, forward delay time, maxage. Every bridge can set the diameter of Bridge, and it is effective when the bridge is root bridge. Effective in the CIST By default, the diameter is 7. The value of hwMstpDiameter is only unused(65535) when it is read.
hwMstpDiameter.name: hwMstpDiameter

hwMstpEdgedPortDefault.description: When the stp edged-port default is enabled. By default,the port enabled stp is edged-port .
hwMstpEdgedPortDefault.name: hwMstpEdgedPortDefault

hwMstpForceVersion.description: The mode of this Bridge spanning-tree protocol. At present, the bridge hold out STP compatible mode and MSTP . User can set the mode by command line. By default, the mode is MSTP.
hwMstpForceVersion.name: hwMstpForceVersion

hwMstpInstanceEntry.description: The table includes the information of the instance. The index of the table is Multiple spanning-tree instance Identifier.
hwMstpInstanceEntry.name: hwMstpInstanceEntry

hwMstpInstanceID.description: Multiple spanning-tree instance Identifier. The scope of instance identifier is different, some versions are 0 to 48.
hwMstpInstanceID.name: hwMstpInstanceID

hwMstpInstanceInfoGroup.description: A collection of objects describes the attribute of the instance in the multi spanning tree protocol.
hwMstpInstanceInfoGroup.name: hwMstpInstanceInfoGroup

hwMstpInstanceTable.description: The table includes the information of the instance.
hwMstpInstanceTable.name: hwMstpInstanceTable

hwMstpMasterBridgeID.description: The Bridge Identifier of the current Master Bridge. It is the root Bridge Identifier of the instance 0 in the region.
hwMstpMasterBridgeID.name: hwMstpMasterBridgeID

hwMstpMasterPathCost.description: The CIST path cost from the transmitting Bridge to the Master Bridge. By default, the value is 0.
hwMstpMasterPathCost.name: hwMstpMasterPathCost

hwMstpNoAgreementCheck.description: Whether enhance agreement is enabled. When Huawei datacomm devices running the VRP are internetworking with non-Huawei devices, you need to enable this on Huawei devices to configure the mode of the fast transition mechanism the same as that on non-Huawei devices.
hwMstpNoAgreementCheck.name: hwMstpNoAgreementCheck

hwMstpOperFormatSelector.description: The operative Configuration Identifier Format Selector in use by the Bridge. This has a value of 0 indicate the format specified in the Standard of IEEE 802.1s. By default, the value is 0.
hwMstpOperFormatSelector.name: hwMstpOperFormatSelector

hwMstpOperMstID.description: Operative Multiple spanning-tree instance Identifier. The relation between VLAN and Multiple spanning-tree instance is effective in the bridge. The scope of instance identifier is different, some versions are 0 to 48.
hwMstpOperMstID.name: hwMstpOperMstID

hwMstpOperRegionName.description: This MSTP operative region name. It can be used to determine whether the region is the same region with the mapping between VLAN and instance and hwMstpOperRevisionLevel.
hwMstpOperRegionName.name: hwMstpOperRegionName

hwMstpOperRevisionLevel.description: This MSTP operative revision level. It can be used to determine whether the region is the same region with the mapping between VLAN and instance and hwMstpOperRegionName. By default, the value is 0
hwMstpOperRevisionLevel.name: hwMstpOperRevisionLevel

hwMstpPathCostStandard.description: Path cost standard of the bridge. Value dot1d-1998 is IEEE 802.1d standard in 1998, value dot1t is IEEE 802.1t standard, and value legacy is a private legacy standard. The default path cost standard is 2(IEEE 802.1t standard).
hwMstpPathCostStandard.name: hwMstpPathCostStandard

hwMstpPortCompliance.description: The value of this object identifies the protocol format of the MSTP packet sent and received on the port. The protocol format can be one of the following: 1: auto (the self-adaptive protocol format) 2: dotls (the standard IEEE 802.1s format) 3: legacy (the private protocol format) By default, the protocol format of the MSTP packet is self-adaptive, that is, auto(1).
hwMstpPortCompliance.name: hwMstpPortCompliance

hwMstpPortEntry.description: The table includes the information of the port of the multiple spanning tree instance. The index of the table is the aggregation of multiple spanning tree instance identifier and port index.
hwMstpPortEntry.name: hwMstpPortEntry

hwMstpPortInfoGroup.description: A collection of objects is necessary to show the information of the port in the bridge in the multi spanning tree protocol.
hwMstpPortInfoGroup.name: hwMstpPortInfoGroup

hwMstpPortTCNotify.description: The main interface notifies its sub-interfaces to update MAC entries and ARP entries after receiving a TC message. This prevents services from being interrupted.
hwMstpPortTCNotify.name: hwMstpPortTCNotify

hwMstpPortTable.description: The table includes the information of the port of the multiple spanning tree instance.
hwMstpPortTable.name: hwMstpPortTable

hwMstpProBpduGuard.description: Whether BPDU portection is enabled or not on a MSTP process.
hwMstpProBpduGuard.name: hwMstpProBpduGuard

hwMstpProBridgeLostRootPrimary.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when the bridge is no longer the root bridge of the MSTP process Spanning Tree. Another switch with higher priority has already been the root bridge.
hwMstpProBridgeLostRootPrimary.name: hwMstpProBridgeLostRootPrimary

hwMstpProConvergeMode.description: Spanning-Tree converge mode. When the mode is fast, MAC entries and ARP entries will be deleted. When the mode is normal, the entries will be aged.
hwMstpProConvergeMode.name: hwMstpProConvergeMode

hwMstpProDiameter.description: The Spanning-Tree diameter of a MSTP process, the default value is 7. The value of hwMstpProDiameter is only unused(65535) when it is read.
hwMstpProDiameter.name: hwMstpProDiameter

hwMstpProEdgePortChanged.description: When the edged-port receives a BPDU packet, the edged-port attribute will be disabled. Then the SNMP trap is generated.
hwMstpProEdgePortChanged.name: hwMstpProEdgePortChanged

hwMstpProEntry.description: Entry of the MSTP process information table.
hwMstpProEntry.name: hwMstpProEntry

hwMstpProForceVersion.description: Mode of Spanning-Tree portocol on a MSTP process.
hwMstpProForceVersion.name: hwMstpProForceVersion

hwMstpProFwdDelay.description: Forward delay of a MSTP process, the default value is 1500 centiseconds.
hwMstpProFwdDelay.name: hwMstpProFwdDelay

hwMstpProHelloTime.description: Hello time of a MSTP process, the default value is 200 centiseconds.
hwMstpProHelloTime.name: hwMstpProHelloTime

hwMstpProInstanceAdminMappedVlanListHigh.description: The higher part of administrative VLAN list mapped to the spanning tree instance identified by MSTID.
hwMstpProInstanceAdminMappedVlanListHigh.name: hwMstpProInstanceAdminMappedVlanListHigh

hwMstpProInstanceAdminMappedVlanListLow.description: The lower part of administrative VLAN list mapped to the spanning tree instance identified by MSTID.
hwMstpProInstanceAdminMappedVlanListLow.name: hwMstpProInstanceAdminMappedVlanListLow

hwMstpProInstanceBridgeID.description: The Bridge Identifier for the spanning tree instance identified by MSTID.
hwMstpProInstanceBridgeID.name: hwMstpProInstanceBridgeID

hwMstpProInstanceBridgePriority.description: The Bridge Priority for the spanning tree instance identified by MSTID. Step of 4096.For example, we can set the Priority of the bridge such as 0, 4096, 8192 etc. It can be used to determined whether the bridge is the root of the spanning tree.
hwMstpProInstanceBridgePriority.name: hwMstpProInstanceBridgePriority

hwMstpProInstanceDesignedRoot.description: The Bridge Identifier of the Root Bridge for the spanning tree instance identified by MSTID.
hwMstpProInstanceDesignedRoot.name: hwMstpProInstanceDesignedRoot

hwMstpProInstanceEntry.description: The entry of the MSTP process instance information table.
hwMstpProInstanceEntry.name: hwMstpProInstanceEntry

hwMstpProInstanceOperMappedVlanListHigh.description: The higher part of operative VLAN list mapped to the spanning tree instance identified by MSTID.
hwMstpProInstanceOperMappedVlanListHigh.name: hwMstpProInstanceOperMappedVlanListHigh

hwMstpProInstanceOperMappedVlanListLow.description: The lower part of operative VLAN list mapped to the spanning tree instance identified by MSTID.
hwMstpProInstanceOperMappedVlanListLow.name: hwMstpProInstanceOperMappedVlanListLow

hwMstpProInstanceRemainingHops.description: The remaining hops of the spanning tree instance identified by MSTID.
hwMstpProInstanceRemainingHops.name: hwMstpProInstanceRemainingHops

hwMstpProInstanceRootPathCost.description: The path cost from the transmitting Bridge to the Root Bridge for the spanning tree instance identified by MSTID.
hwMstpProInstanceRootPathCost.name: hwMstpProInstanceRootPathCost

hwMstpProInstanceRootPort.description: The root port for the spanning tree instance identified by the MSTID.
hwMstpProInstanceRootPort.name: hwMstpProInstanceRootPort

hwMstpProInstanceRootType.description: Config this Bridge as a primary root or secondary root / cancel the root for this spanning tree instance identified by MSTID. The current value of the hwMstpiRootType is the value that was set recently.
hwMstpProInstanceRootType.name: hwMstpProInstanceRootType

hwMstpProInstanceRowStatus.description: To band MSTI and VLAN List. Operation of CreateAndGo can be used to create a new instance, and operation of Destroy be used to destroy an existent instance. But these operation won't be effective if they are not actived by executing command of active region-configuration or setting mib node of hwMstpRegionConfActive.
hwMstpProInstanceRowStatus.name: hwMstpProInstanceRowStatus

hwMstpProLinkShareGuard.description: Whether the Link-share Guard function is enabled on the MSTP process. If the function is enabled, the root Guard function will also work on port in all instance besides instance 0, when the link between the ports either of which is in Link_share mode broken down.
hwMstpProLinkShareGuard.name: hwMstpProLinkShareGuard

hwMstpProLinkSharePortList.description: The port list participates in the status calculation of a specified MSTP process witch link-share method.
hwMstpProLinkSharePortList.name: hwMstpProLinkSharePortList

hwMstpProLoopbackDetected.description: When port detected loopback, block the port and arise trap.
hwMstpProLoopbackDetected.name: hwMstpProLoopbackDetected

hwMstpProMCheck.description: Whether to do Mcheck function on a MSTP process.
hwMstpProMCheck.name: hwMstpProMCheck

hwMstpProMaxAge.description: Max age of a MSTP process, the default value is 2000 centiseconds.
hwMstpProMaxAge.name: hwMstpProMaxAge

hwMstpProMaxHops.description: Maxhops of a MSTP process, the default value is 20.
hwMstpProMaxHops.name: hwMstpProMaxHops

hwMstpProNewBridgeLostRootPrimary.description: Specify that the switch loses the position of root bridge in MSTP process.
hwMstpProNewBridgeLostRootPrimary.name: hwMstpProNewBridgeLostRootPrimary

hwMstpProNewEdgePortChanged.description: Specify that the edge port is invalid because of receiving a BPDU packet.
hwMstpProNewEdgePortChanged.name: hwMstpProNewEdgePortChanged

hwMstpProNewPortBpduEncapsulation.description: The value of this object identifies the protocol format of the BPDU sent on the port. The protocol format can be one of the following: 1: pvst (the PVST format) 2: stp (the STP format) By default, the BPDU format of the MSTP packet is stp(2).
hwMstpProNewPortBpduEncapsulation.name: hwMstpProNewPortBpduEncapsulation

hwMstpProNewPortBpduFilter.description: Whether the port BPDU-filter is enabled. By default, there is no configuration on the port. The port will not send or receive BPDUs.
hwMstpProNewPortBpduFilter.name: hwMstpProNewPortBpduFilter

hwMstpProNewPortBpduGuarded.description: Specify that the edge port receives the BPDU packets when BPDU protection was enabled in MSTP process.
hwMstpProNewPortBpduGuarded.name: hwMstpProNewPortBpduGuarded

hwMstpProNewPortBpduVlan.description: The VLAN of port is BPDU VLAN.
hwMstpProNewPortBpduVlan.name: hwMstpProNewPortBpduVlan

hwMstpProNewPortCompliance.description: The value of this object identifies the protocol format of the MSTP packet sent and received on the port. The protocol format can be one of the following: 1: auto (the self-adaptive protocol format) 2: dotls (the standard IEEE 802.1s format) 3: legacy (the private protocol format) By default, the protocol format of the MSTP packet is self-adaptive, that is, auto(1).
hwMstpProNewPortCompliance.name: hwMstpProNewPortCompliance

hwMstpProNewPortConfigDigestSnooping.description: This object indicates whether the digest snooping function is enabled on the port: 1: enabled 2: disabled By default, the function is not enabled. In other words, the default value is disabled(2).
hwMstpProNewPortConfigDigestSnooping.name: hwMstpProNewPortConfigDigestSnooping

hwMstpProNewPortDesignatedBridge.description: The Bridge Identifier of the bridge which this port considers to be the Designated Bridge for this port's segment.
hwMstpProNewPortDesignatedBridge.name: hwMstpProNewPortDesignatedBridge

hwMstpProNewPortDesignatedCost.description: The path cost of the designated port of the segment connected to this port. This value is compared to the Root Path Cost field in received bridge BPDUs.
hwMstpProNewPortDesignatedCost.name: hwMstpProNewPortDesignatedCost

hwMstpProNewPortDesignatedPort.description: The port identifier of the port on the Designated Bridge for this port's segment.
hwMstpProNewPortDesignatedPort.name: hwMstpProNewPortDesignatedPort

hwMstpProNewPortDesignatedRoot.description: The Bridge Identifier of the Root Bridge for the port of the MSTP process Spanning Tree.
hwMstpProNewPortDesignatedRoot.name: hwMstpProNewPortDesignatedRoot

hwMstpProNewPortEntry.description: The entry of the MSTP process port information table.
hwMstpProNewPortEntry.name: hwMstpProNewPortEntry

hwMstpProNewPortLoopGuard.description: Whether the loop protection is enabled.
hwMstpProNewPortLoopGuard.name: hwMstpProNewPortLoopGuard

hwMstpProNewPortLoopGuarded.description: Specify that the root port has not received any BPDU packets for a long time when loop protection is enabled in MSTP process.
hwMstpProNewPortLoopGuarded.name: hwMstpProNewPortLoopGuarded

hwMstpProNewPortNoAgreementCheck.description: Whether enhance agreement is enabled. When Huawei datacomm devices running the VRP are internetworking with non-Huawei devices, you need to enable this on Huawei devices to configure the mode of the fast transition mechanism the same as that on non-Huawei devices.
hwMstpProNewPortNoAgreementCheck.name: hwMstpProNewPortNoAgreementCheck

hwMstpProNewPortPathCost.description: The path cost of paths with which the package passes the port. The range of path cost is 1..65535 for 802.1d standard, is 1..200000000 for 802.1t standard, and is 1..200000 for the legacy standard.
hwMstpProNewPortPathCost.name: hwMstpProNewPortPathCost

hwMstpProNewPortPriority.description: The value of the priority field which is contained in the first (in network byte order) four bits of the (2 octet long) Port ID. The other octet of the Port ID is given by the value of hwMstpiPortIndex. And step of 16. It is the priority of the port in the MSTP process, and it can be used to determine the role of the port in the MSTP process Spanning Tree.
hwMstpProNewPortPriority.name: hwMstpProNewPortPriority

hwMstpProNewPortRole.description: Indicates the port role on a particular instance.
hwMstpProNewPortRole.name: hwMstpProNewPortRole

hwMstpProNewPortRootGuard.description: Whether the root guard is enabled. The function is to prevent the port from receiving the BPDUs, the priority of which is above the priority of the port.
hwMstpProNewPortRootGuard.name: hwMstpProNewPortRootGuard

hwMstpProNewPortRootGuarded.description: Specify that a designated port receives a BPDU packet with the priority higher than that of the root bridge when root bridge protection is enabled in MSTP process.
hwMstpProNewPortRootGuarded.name: hwMstpProNewPortRootGuarded

hwMstpProNewPortState.description: The current state of the port in MSTP process. It must be disabled, discarding, learning or forwarding.
hwMstpProNewPortState.name: hwMstpProNewPortState

hwMstpProNewPortStateDiscarding.description: Specify that the status of the port STP becomes Discarding in MSTP process.
hwMstpProNewPortStateDiscarding.name: hwMstpProNewPortStateDiscarding

hwMstpProNewPortStateForwarding.description: Specify that the status of the port STP becomes Forwarding in MSTP process.
hwMstpProNewPortStateForwarding.name: hwMstpProNewPortStateForwarding

hwMstpProNewPortStpClearStatistics.description: Clear the Spanning Tree statistics in specified MSTP process. The value is unused(65535) when it is read. The value must be clear(1) when it is set.
hwMstpProNewPortStpClearStatistics.name: hwMstpProNewPortStpClearStatistics

hwMstpProNewPortStpEdgeport.description: Whether the port fast is enabled in the MSTP process. By default, there is no configuration on the port. When the port is the edge port, it can change to forwarding state immediately.
hwMstpProNewPortStpEdgeport.name: hwMstpProNewPortStpEdgeport

hwMstpProNewPortStpMcheck.description: When root interface is changed from STP mode to RSTP or MSTP mode, the appointed interface can not switch to RSTP or MSTP mode automatically. At the time, you need switch back with hand by set Mcheck value to enable(1). The value unused(65535) when it is read.
hwMstpProNewPortStpMcheck.name: hwMstpProNewPortStpMcheck

hwMstpProNewPortStpPointToPoint.description: Whether the port connects the point to point link. If user set the port as a point to point port, the port is a point to point port in the MSTP process. If user set the port as a point to point port but the port isn't, the mstp may import temporary loop. So user can use the default.
hwMstpProNewPortStpPointToPoint.name: hwMstpProNewPortStpPointToPoint

hwMstpProNewPortStpRXMSTPBPDU.description: The number of received MST BPDUs.
hwMstpProNewPortStpRXMSTPBPDU.name: hwMstpProNewPortStpRXMSTPBPDU

hwMstpProNewPortStpRXRSTPBPDU.description: The number of received RST BPDUs.
hwMstpProNewPortStpRXRSTPBPDU.name: hwMstpProNewPortStpRXRSTPBPDU

hwMstpProNewPortStpRXStpBPDU.description: The number of received Config BPDUs.
hwMstpProNewPortStpRXStpBPDU.name: hwMstpProNewPortStpRXStpBPDU

hwMstpProNewPortStpRXTC.description: The number of TC BPDUs received by the port.
hwMstpProNewPortStpRXTC.name: hwMstpProNewPortStpRXTC

hwMstpProNewPortStpRXTCNBPDU.description: The number of received TCN BPDUs.
hwMstpProNewPortStpRXTCNBPDU.name: hwMstpProNewPortStpRXTCNBPDU

hwMstpProNewPortStpStatus.description: Whether the Spanning Tree Protocol is enabled on this port.
hwMstpProNewPortStpStatus.name: hwMstpProNewPortStpStatus

hwMstpProNewPortStpTXMSTPBPDU.description: The number of transmitted MST BPDUs.
hwMstpProNewPortStpTXMSTPBPDU.name: hwMstpProNewPortStpTXMSTPBPDU

hwMstpProNewPortStpTXRSTPBPDU.description: The number of transmitted RST BPDUs.
hwMstpProNewPortStpTXRSTPBPDU.name: hwMstpProNewPortStpTXRSTPBPDU

hwMstpProNewPortStpTXStpBPDU.description: The number of transmitted Config BPDUs.
hwMstpProNewPortStpTXStpBPDU.name: hwMstpProNewPortStpTXStpBPDU

hwMstpProNewPortStpTXTC.description: The number of TC BPDUs sent by the port.
hwMstpProNewPortStpTXTC.name: hwMstpProNewPortStpTXTC

hwMstpProNewPortStpTXTCNBPDU.description: The number of transmitted TCN BPDUs.
hwMstpProNewPortStpTXTCNBPDU.name: hwMstpProNewPortStpTXTCNBPDU

hwMstpProNewPortStpTransLimit.description: The value is used to set BPDU maximum transmission rate of the port. If value is set 0, the transmit limit of the port is equal to the wMstpTransmitLimitDefault value
hwMstpProNewPortStpTransLimit.name: hwMstpProNewPortStpTransLimit

hwMstpProNewPortTable.description: The table includes the information of the port of the MSTP process.
hwMstpProNewPortTable.name: hwMstpProNewPortTable

hwMstpProNewPortType.description: An interface to participate in the status calculation of link-share , no-link-share or no-link-share with VLAN Spanning Tree processes.
hwMstpProNewPortType.name: hwMstpProNewPortType

hwMstpProNewPortVplsSubinterfaceEnable.description: The main interface notifies its sub-interfaces to update MAC entries and ARP entries after receiving a TC message. This prevents services from being interrupted.
hwMstpProNewPortVplsSubinterfaceEnable.name: hwMstpProNewPortVplsSubinterfaceEnable

hwMstpProNoLinkSharePortList.description: The port list participates in the status calculation of a specified MSTP process witch no-link-share method.
hwMstpProNoLinkSharePortList.name: hwMstpProNoLinkSharePortList

hwMstpProPathCostStandard.description: Path cost standard of a MSTP process, the fault value is dot1t.
hwMstpProPathCostStandard.name: hwMstpProPathCostStandard

hwMstpProPortBpduGuarded.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when an edged port of the BPDU-guard MSTP process receives BPDU packets.
hwMstpProPortBpduGuarded.name: hwMstpProPortBpduGuarded

hwMstpProPortCompliance.description: The value of this object identifies the protocol format of the MSTP packet sent and received on the port. The protocol format can be one of the following: 1: auto (the self-adaptive protocol format) 2: dotls (the standard IEEE 802.1s format) 3: legacy (the private protocol format) By default, the protocol format of the MSTP packet is self-adaptive, that is, auto(1).
hwMstpProPortCompliance.name: hwMstpProPortCompliance

hwMstpProPortConfigDigestSnooping.description: This object indicates whether the digest snooping function is enabled on the port: 1: enabled 2: disabled By default, the function is not enabled. In other words, the default value is disabled(2).
hwMstpProPortConfigDigestSnooping.name: hwMstpProPortConfigDigestSnooping

hwMstpProPortDesignatedBridge.description: The Bridge Identifier of the bridge which this port considers to be the Designated Bridge for this port's segment.
hwMstpProPortDesignatedBridge.name: hwMstpProPortDesignatedBridge

hwMstpProPortDesignatedCost.description: The path cost of the designated port of the segment connected to this port. This value is compared to the Root Path Cost field in received bridge BPDUs.
hwMstpProPortDesignatedCost.name: hwMstpProPortDesignatedCost

hwMstpProPortDesignatedPort.description: The Port Identifier of the port on the Designated Bridge for this port's segment.
hwMstpProPortDesignatedPort.name: hwMstpProPortDesignatedPort

hwMstpProPortDesignatedRoot.description: The Bridge Identifier of the Root Bridge for the port of the MSTP process Spanning Tree.
